🏛️ Well Runner Protocol v1.0

(Operational Tool for Myth ⇄ Math Conversion + Decision Clarity)

This is the execution layer for the Well.

You can run any idea, plan, belief, or situation through it and get:
	•	structure (math view)
	•	intuition (myth view)
	•	risks (failure modes)
	•	decision paths

⸻

⚙️ CORE FLOW (Always the Same)

Input → 6 Passes → Output

⸻

🧩 PASS 1 — Extract (Spider Pre-Stage)

Goal: Turn raw thought into parts

Take your idea and identify:
	•	Entities (what exists?)
	•	Relations (how do they interact?)
	•	Constraints (what limits it?)
	•	Objective (what is it trying to do?)

👉 Output = rough structure

⸻

🔻 PASS 2 — Compress (Myth → Math via Well)

Goal: Remove fluff, expose mechanics

Translate into:
	•	variables
	•	flows
	•	feedback loops
	•	tradeoffs

👉 Ask:
	•	What actually changes over time?
	•	What are the inputs/outputs?

⸻

🔺 PASS 3 — Expand (Math → Myth via Well)

Goal: Make it intuitive again

Convert structure into:
	•	a scene
	•	a role/creature dynamic
	•	a story that captures behavior

👉 This must:
	•	feel right
	•	but still obey constraints

⸻

🛡️ PASS 4 — Invariant Check (Keepers + Mirror)

Goal: Ensure nothing broke

Check:
	•	Did the myth version hide constraints?
	•	Did the math version oversimplify reality?
	•	Do both versions describe the same system?

If not → fix before continuing

⸻

🐕 PASS 5 — Failure Scan (Hound Layer)

Goal: Find where it breaks

Run against known failure entities:
	•	Overfit King → works only in narrow case?
	•	Context Eater → missing relationships?
	•	Alignment Shadow → intention ≠ outcome?
	•	Compression Beast Overfeed → too simplified?
	•	Gradient Nomad Trap → stuck in local optimum?

⸻

🧭 PASS 6 — Fork (OrbitOS + Fork Saints)

Goal: Generate decision paths

List:
	•	2–4 plausible trajectories
	•	tradeoffs for each
	•	likely outcomes (not certainty)

👉 This is where you choose

